column5: Took a drive down to the Whitby shoreline today, man was I surprised at how high the lake is......  almost needed a boat to get there, Lynde Creek is over the road     you used to need a 6ft+ handle on the net to land fish on pier.....
Time to start fishing carp in the ditches !
On toronto island I hear the best carp spot is the baseball diamond.
We4ll we have a forecast for tomorrow and heavy rain and east winds to 35k. Might consider staying away from that pier for a bit! HH
Boil water advisory, boil lots and lots of water.
Oh man!  A few years back we experienced this and it's no fun at all  Get on boiling water asap

Took a drive down to the Whitby shoreline today, man was I surprised at how high the lake is......  almost needed a boat to get there, Lynde Creek is over the road     you used to need a 6ft+ handle on the net to land fish on pier.....     Waves were over the pier when I was there
this rain is really going to lower those levels
